.TH "firmware_loading_store" 9 "firmware_loading_store" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
firmware_loading_store \- set value in the 'loading' control file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" firmware_loading_store
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device pointer
.IP "attr" 12
device attribute pointer
.IP "buf" 12
buffer to scan for loading control value
.IP "count" 12
number of bytes in \fIbuf\fP

The relevant values are:

1: Start a load, discarding any previous partial load.
0: Conclude the load and hand the data to the driver code.
-1: Conclude the load with an error and discard any written data.
